SCOTLAND'S largest power station may have to close due to the huge sums its operator must pay to connect to the national grid. Grid threat to power plant SCOTLAND'S largest power station may have to close due to the huge sums its operator must pay to connect to the national grid.Scottish Power, which owns Longannet in Fife, said financial changes were needed to avert the threat of closure.Longannet is one of the biggest coal-fired power stations in Europe. 